<hl>
<seg id=1> Do Advertisement for Pfizer, Dole Appeal People to Pay More Attention to Impotence </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Associated Press Ltd.,New York) - Republican Dole, who once contended president position in 1996, will start a new campaign. This time he will do advertisement for Pfizer Company, the manufacturer of world famous aphrodyne Viagra and appeal people to pay more attention to impotence. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> Dole will talk much in TV ad and focus on sex disability and educational ad on men's general health. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> Pfizer would not disclose how much they pay to Dole, and Dole will not mention the name of Viagra in the ad either. </seg>
<seg id=5> This ad will be broadcasted in the beginning of next year. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> Dole's ad is the first time for Pfizer to promote sales of Viagra through TV. </seg>
<seg id=7> Pfizer is considering whether they would make any ad directly mention the name of Viagra. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> In May this year, Dole confessed his trial use of Viagra and spoke highly of its effect as "panacea ". </seg>
<seg id=9> In his statement, Dole said:" I believe that this campaign will help the men to pay more attention to their healthy problem they are afraid to discuss." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Since this aphrodyne came into the market in April this year, American doctors have written more than six million prescriptions of Viagra. </seg>
<seg id=11> In U.S., there are 10 to 20 million men suffer from impotence, of which only 10% go to see a doctor. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> Dole once attend a discussion program, and claimed in parliament to appeal his countrymen to diagnosis and treat prostate cancer in its early stage and understand its side effect - impotence. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=13> Dole was found the prostate cancer in 1991, the doctors said he was healed after an operation. </seg>
</p>
